An arrest has been made over the death of a man in a Glasgow flat.
Police had been called to reports of a disturbance in a flat in Benalder Street, Partick, at 08:50 on Saturday. 
They found a 29-year-old man seriously injured. He was treated by paramedics but died at the scene.
Officers described the death as &quot;suspicious&quot; and launched an investigation. A 23-year-old man has now been arrested in connection with the death.
A report will be sent to the procurator fiscal and the man is due to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday. 
Police said a 25-year-old woman was also injured in the incident and is being treated at Glasgow's Western Infirmary.
